OL,3,CPolice involved in car crash that
OL,4,Ckilled pedestrian 'acted appropriately'
OL,6,F"We found that they had acted
OL,7,Fappropriately and in line with police
OL,8,Fpolicies and procedures. There was no
OL,9,Findication they had behaved in a
OL,10,Fmanner that would justify the bringing
OL,11,Fof disciplinary proceedings, or
OL,12,Fcommitted a criminal offence.
OL,14,F"We provided the coroner with our
OL,15,Finvestigation report to assist with
OL,16,Fthe inquest proceedings and help
OL,17,Fprovide answers to any questions about
OL,18,Fwhat happened that evening."
